snippet: Stephen Curry had 25 points and six assists, Klay Thompson scored 21 points and the Golden State Warriors shook off a two-game losing streak by rolling past the lowly Minnesota Timberwolves, 110-97 on Saturday night....

headline.print_headline: Warriors Shake Off Skid, Beat Timberwolves 110-97
